<seg id=1> Jiang Zeming Highlights the Importance of Milita and Reserve Duty Work </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News Agency. Beijing. September 1. (Reporter Ge Yumin) Jiang Zeming, General Secretary of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China, President of the People's Republic of China, Chairman of Central Military Commission, stressed,  while meeting with representitives attending the national conference on militia and reserve duty work, that regional Party committees, governments and military departments at all levels, while taking the interests of the whole nation and the whole Party into account, working for the country's ever-lasting stability, should pay attention to the militia and reserve duty work. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> Jiang Zeming pointed out that the militia are both civilians and soldiers; not only a main force in defending the national security and the country's integrity,but also a main force in guarding the social stability and promoting the material and spiritual prosperity. </seg>
<seg id=4> Regional Party committees, goverments and military departments at all levels should bring into full play the zeal and creativity of the milita and the reserve forces so that they can make their contributions to the reform, development and stability of the society. </seg>
<seg id=5> All military units should guarantee the reform, development and stability of the society while participating in the construction of regional economy and working towards the common prosperity of all nationalities. </seg>
<seg id=6> We must strengthen the unity between the military units and the governments, and that between the military units and the civilians,to enable the military units really understand, stand with and for the people of every nationality. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> Liu Huaqing, vice President of Central Military Commission, members of Military Commission, Zhang Wannian,Yu Yongbo, Fu Quanyou and directors from Headquarters of the General Staff Of People's Liberation Army (PLA), General Political Department of PLA, General Logistics Department of PLA and General Office of Central Military Commission are present during the meeting. </seg>
</p>
